@node Preface "Preface"

   As almost every Amiga program, MaxManager gives you the ARexx control
 possibility, the thing Bill Gate$ haven't 'invented' yet (and therefore
 we got no 'revolutionary break-thru' in the world today yet). ARexx port
 gives you possibility to automatize loads of processes you used to do
 manually like file tossing for instance (take a look at the example
 AminetTosser.rexx script), or removing outdated files (or pee-see crap
 taking your HDD like: whoaa.arj 700K "Whoaa scream sound for Windows"
 (authentic - it was even more because whoaa.arj was 1/4 part of
 multivolume archve - about 700K each file!).

@ENDNODE

@node CMD_ABOUT "ABOUT"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
       ABOUT -- Opens ABOUT requester

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} 
       ABOUT

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub} 
       Opens program ABOUT requester and waits for response

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub} 
       None

   @{b}OUTPUTS@{ub} 
       None

@endnode

@node CMD_ADD_DESC_MODE "ADD_DESC_MODE"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
       ADD_DESC_MODE

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} 
       ADD_DESC_MODE MODE/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
       Set Prefs's "NEW/SETTINGS/Description of the file" switch
       to given mode

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub} 
       Mode:
             0 - "Always use descriptions"
             1 - "Use file comment if exists"
             2 - "Always use file comment"

   @{b}OUTPUTS@{ub} 
       RC contains previous state of the switch

@endnode

@node CMD_ADD_MODE "ADD_MODE"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
       ADD_MODE

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} 
       ADD_MODE MODE/N

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub} 
       Set Prefs's "NEW/SETTINGS/While adding new files" switch
       to given mode

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub} 
       Mode:
             0 - "Add and copy"
             1 - "Add and move"
             2 - "Only add"

   @{b}OUTPUTS@{ub} 
       RC contains previous state of the switch

@endnode

@node CMD_ALL "ALL"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
       ALL

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} 
       ALL

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub} 
       Selects all entries in Source listview (as ALL button)

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub} 
       None

   @{b}OUTPUTS@{ub} 
       Number of selected entries

@endnode

@node CMD_DEF_DESC "DEF_DESC"

   @{b}NAME@{ub}
       DEF_DESC

   @{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub} 
       DEF_DESC DESCRIPTION/A

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub} 
       Sets default description (Prefs: "NEW/SETTINGS/Description")

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
       Description you want to become default

   @{b}OUTPUTS@{ub} 
       None

@endnode

